reviews.text: The toilets at this station must be the worse in the country.  It stinks and is always dirty and mostly out of order.  Really bad for a good area.

Time tabling for the district line is a joke. Get the district line from this station of you want to be guaranteed. Staff don’t know when trains are leaving, train drivers leave when they want. No updates for customers. Ridiculous waste of time and you will set yourself back at least 20 mins just waiting at the station because you don’t know which train will be leaving and neither do the staff.

Got a "fantastic" run this morning from platform to platform due to a mess(like always) with a information screen and announcements. Thanks a lot for missing my train. Such a "brilliant" service for the most expensive tube in the world!

14/07 District line 7.25am train to Edgware road was on the platform. Empty.Cancelled AGAIN!!!!. No notification or any information. So predictable!! Thanks

19/07 District line. 7.26 train to Edgware road, information on the screen did not match with the first train leaving the platform.Again!))

Very rude staff. I asked for help, I couldn't understand what he told me. I asked him if he could please repeat it again.He said 'Listen to me...' with the most unfriendly manner. He shouldn't be there. His job is to help people when/if needed, if he is not happy there then  he needs to change job!!!! If you are tired or would prefer to be somewhere else, It's not my fault!!!! 😤
There is on station public toilet  but when district line not working-toilets are closed!!! What if you are train or tram user????
